'''Denis Lawson''' (born [[September 27]], [[1940s#1947|1947]]) is an actor who portrayed [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|rebellion]] [[pilot]] [[Wedge Antilles]] in all three films of the [[original trilogy]]. Coincidentally, he is the maternal uncle of [[Ewan McGregor]], who portrayed [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] throughout the [[prequel trilogy]]. Outside ''[[Star Wars]]'' , the actor is famous for starring in the [[1983]] Scottish film [[Wikipedia:Local Hero|''Local Hero'']] and the [[2005]] BBC television serial [[Wikipedia:Bleak House (2005 TV serial)|''Bleak House'']].

In [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], Lawson's voice was dubbed by [[David Ankrum]]. He reprised the role, in voice-over form, in the Nintendo GameCube game ''[[Star Wars: Rogue Squadron II: Rogue Leader]]''. Lawson's voice also provided the narration for the audio book of ''[[Heir to the Empire]]'' and ''[[Dark Force Rising]]'' in both novels, he reprised his role as Wedge Antilles as well as playing all characters. Lawson turned down [[George Lucas]]'s proposal to make a cameo as [[Captain]] [[Raymus Antilles]] in [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']].

Lawson was approached to return as Wedge Antilles for [[Star Wars: Episode VII The Force Awakens|''Star Wars'': Episode VII ''The Force Awakens'']], but declined, stating that it "just would have bored [him]."<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://www.thecourier.co.uk/news/local/perth-kinross/237277/new-star-wars-films-would-have-bored-me-says-scots-actor-denis-lawson|text=New Star Wars films 'would have bored me', says Scots actor Denis Lawson|author=Kirsty McIntosh|date=2014-05-05|work=[[Wikipedia:The Courier (Dundee)|''The Courier'']]|archivedate=20180725111954}}</ref> However, Lawson later claimed that he actually declined to appear in ''The Force Awakens'' due to a scheduling conflict and would have appeared in the film if he had been available.<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://www.bleedingcool.com/2017/12/09/denis-lawson-wedge-antilles-star-wars|text=Denis Lawson, Wedge Antilles from Star Wars, Did Not Reject Doing the New Films After All|author=Rich Johnston|date=2017-12-09|archivedate=20200118122723}}</ref> He finally returned to the role in [[2019]]'s [[Star Wars: Episode IX The Rise of Skywalker|''Star Wars'': Episode IX ''The Rise of Skywalker'']].

Lawson later voiced Wedge Antilles in the video game ''[[Star Wars: Squadrons]]'' and the animation series ''[[Star Wars: Visions]]''.

